tracks.tag_list: Venturian-Tale Venturian adventurous progessive synths strings guitars powerful epic arpreggios
tracks.title: Strangled
tracks.description: A powerful track which starts out soft and dancy, but then progresses into extreme head-bangin' tension

tracks.tag_list: wailing screaming distortion fast hard loud horror intense laughing techno dance rave wah-wah dark command&conquer
tracks.title: Wicked
tracks.description: Wicked is a fast-paced industrial-techno song with a dark theme.  Inspired by the original command & conquer video game.

tracks.tag_list: intense chasing fighting scary triumphant pushing epic
tracks.title: Driven
tracks.description: This song has many different parts to it, so while it's not repetitive, it holds a strong theme that I find extremely intense. The song could be used in fighting games, racing games, or puzzle games with a high intensity(short timed levels, etc). The song takes you on a trip, and so the title "Driven" has come from the very feeling I get from it. I get the feeling as though I'm being chased, either by time itself or something very, very scary. It has somewhat of a dark sound, while at the same time triumphant, as if it is pushing for an unsure yet determined protagonist.

tracks.tag_list: dark progressive chasing fighting intense fast-paced urgent
tracks.title: Tunneled
tracks.description: Tunneled starts off with a catchy bass line then into a dark opus signifying the stress of being chased through a dark tunnel with the only option of going forward as fast as possible.  As the song progresses a short interlude breaks in then it bounces back into the "chase" theme given from the get-go.  The song has many different parts, and pieces of it could be used for various breaks in videos.  Being a fast-paced action song, it would do well in conjunction with any theme stressing urgency with dark overtones.

tracks.tag_list: fast sequencer synths loops chippy
tracks.title: Trial by fire
tracks.description: An intense techno tune that takes you on a trip through pure madness!  This song evokes the emotion of fighting or hardcore dance.  You can expect a bit of an adrenaline rush if you like techno or rave style music.  The song would do great in a fight sequence during a video game or short film.  Enjoy!

tracks.tag_list: moody conflicting confusing sectional catchy quirky electronic panning suspensful sway hip-hop pop techno chippy
tracks.title: Trade Off
tracks.description: Techno, Pop, Chip Tunes, and Hip Hop all in one.  This song brings in a catchy melody that elevates the mood.  Transitional sections bring the mood back down to a neutral sway, with just a hint of underlying sadness carrying the smiling chip tune through the end.  The tune is quite catchy, so it would do well in a spot where it compliments rather than interrupts the whole experience.

tracks.tag_list: sci-fi rpg fantasy delayers apreggiator synths mysterious slow
tracks.title: Time was flying by
tracks.description: This song has a slow beat, driven by a melodic chain of tunes that convey a message of "mystery" and science fiction.  I would very much see this in a futuristic RTS/RPG/Space Flight Sim Game, but it could be used for just about anything else that wants a complimentary song that says "Mystery" or "Fantasy"

tracks.tag_list: bells delayers reverb mysterious
tracks.title: The Hall
tracks.description: The Hall is a slow, melodic song that gives the experience of uncovering a mystery

tracks.tag_list: bells moving dark mysterious synths drums slow
tracks.title: The hall (redux)
tracks.description: This is a haunting revisit of "The Hall" - While some like the original, I thought I'd make a few modifications.  There is now a stronger bassline, and I've lowered the volume and pitch on some of the bells towards the end.  It was commented that the high-pitched bells were too abrasive, and that there wasn't enough bass.  Give this chilling song a listen and let me know what you think!

tracks.tag_list: moody tranquil background guitars strings thick
tracks.title: Temperence
tracks.description: Temperence is a song that starts off slow, using rich strings (guitar/orchestral) with a thick melody.  The mood it conveys is tranquil, and makes for good background music.

tracks.tag_list: slow ambient tranquil background strings guitars
tracks.title: Temperence version 2
tracks.description: Temperence is a song that starts off slow, using rich strings (guitar/orchestral) with a thick melody.  The mood it conveys is tranquil, and makes for good background music.

tracks.tag_list: hulk-smash funky short upbeat fast happy LOUD arpeggio
tracks.title: Stunt
tracks.description: A short up-beat funky tune - fast paced with a sense of excitement.

tracks.tag_list: loops agressive synths strings smooth groovy urban
tracks.title: Street Lights
tracks.description: A passive electronica song with a hip hop influence.  The song seamlessly loops even with it's featured intro and outtro.  It contains a slightly aggressive hip-hop beat with light synths and strings that smooth out the edges.

tracks.tag_list: strings synths guitars distortion reverb mystery adventure fantasy waiting intermittent
tracks.title: Wouldn't it be
tracks.description: I should have named this, what could be, because this song is shrouded with an epic, fantasy feel.  The distorted guitar conveys a more modern fantasy, but it is still very much a song devoted to anything RPG or futuristic.  The slow beat drives the melody into a world of mystery, and anything you use that would like to compliment your mysterious feel; this one is definitely worth a try.

tracks.tag_list: thoughtful reflective somber dark background
tracks.title: Put in Stone
tracks.description: Put in Stone has a driving beat held up by the sound of a hammer hitting an anvil all the way through. The distorted guitar's melody plays along nicely as the high-synths layered over top convey a melody of "Mystery" or "Fantasy". The song is not at all overwhelming, but much more consistent and good for something going on in the background to compliment mechanics of menu-driven gameplay or an open-ended message that inspires the listener to "think"

tracks.tag_list: espionage spy spyvsspy upbeat catchy quirky
tracks.title: Spy vs Spy
tracks.description: It's a playful tune I'd like to hear as black and white connive and scheme. The song has a hip hop beat along with a catchy bass line hooked to a chain of different melodies all shouting espionage! Check it!

tracks.tag_list: disorienting background music progessive captivating moody dark
tracks.title: Slipped
tracks.description: Slipped is a slower song with a strong melody in which I'm proud of.  It uses high variations in tune and drums, and would make a great background song for a game or video!

tracks.tag_list: slow distortion guitars short
tracks.title: Rock it OUT
tracks.description: Rock it Out is a slow 2 - 4 beat driven by both electric guitar and heavy distorted guitar. The electric guitar is somewhat soft and melodic, while the heavy guitar blasts in with presence.

tracks.tag_list: warm bright upbeat fast powerful majestic happy beautiful
tracks.title: Rising Sun
tracks.description: A warm break-beat song including a bright melody.  The theme is up-beat, entrancing, and quite powerful.  Enjoy!

tracks.tag_list: funky funk jammin' upbeat lifting groovy
tracks.title: Right Where I want You!
tracks.description: Right where I want you has such an expression of getting something much desired.  It also conveys a feeling confidence, exploration, and being too damn cool.  the song would made great for a menu selection screen, or perhaps a song in a sim game when things are going well, or where the theme is "hip" - it contains a mix of break-beat / hip hop samples,

tracks.tag_list: loops rpg potion-shop video-game short-loop
tracks.title: Potion shop
tracks.description: The young hero needs to hear happy music while he shops for potions and magical items so he can finally win the game.

tracks.tag_list: dark icy cold ackward synths strings rich adventure rpgmusic
tracks.title: Ooze
tracks.description: Ooze is a dark & ackward tune that may compliment any theme in regards to something unclear.  The song has a rich drumkit, a driving ambience and strong synths that push said theme from beginning to end.  The music gives me the sense that something is unclear, unknown, but there is an uneasy tension building.  It would be very well used in a dungeon of an RPG, a production part of a strategy game, or a dark-themed puzzler. Please rate this song and post comments! Thank you!

tracks.tag_list: pitter-patter steady synths strings magical mysterious exciting rpgmusic
tracks.title: Once upon a time in...
tracks.description: A steady beat driven by the patter of drums & hard synths taking you to a magical place of wonder!  The melody covers a few octaves hitting almost every note, including a strong chorus that'll stick in your ears.  The feeling evokes a sense of mystery, enticement, and magic.

tracks.tag_list: funky nostalgia breakbeat repetitive amateur
tracks.title: Nintendo was cool
tracks.description: I loved my NES and SNES back in the day.  After the N64, mehhhh. Anyway: This song is devoted to a fun nintendo beat mixed with a modern funk guitar along with a breakbeat.  The nintendo melody plays through different parts, and the song switches a few times to showcase the funk!  The song all together has quite a retro feel, with a hint of modernization thus making it nostalgic, yet useable for something more modern-retro-esque.

tracks.tag_list: sim-city slow ominous mysterious building strong synths strings
tracks.title: Morning
tracks.description: A strong piece with many different parts to it.  The song starts off a bit slow and ominous, and as it continues to play to a bit of mysterious feel it finally ends in a triumphant opus.

tracks.tag_list: synths rockin' fun thrashing crazy special
tracks.title: Mad, Mad Men
tracks.description: This rockin' tune features the use of synth lead guitars and fast thrashing drums.  Many different parts keep it from being repetitive, and it's intensity builds into a release of strong melody.  This was my first song using synth leads, and so it was very difficult to put together and took 3 days to finish.  It's rapid pace would make it ideal for racing games, or something with a theme needing highly intense music.  It also seamlessly loops perfectly.

tracks.tag_list: synths apreggios skips hard hardcore intense agressive powerful fast
tracks.title: Machine One
tracks.description: One of my personal favorites. As I added each instrument I let the song tell me what it wanted to do. Inspired by dubstep, techno, video games, and trance.   I'm really happy with what I ended up with, and it was a lot of hard work mastering and working out parts that didn't sound right to me.

tracks.tag_list: heavy synths agressive lost strong slow
tracks.title: Lost
tracks.description: This one is a heavy, slow, yet aggressive electronic opus.  Filled with many different parts, this song conveys the feeling of being lost, yet giving strong convincing feelings of accomplishment.

tracks.tag_list: chirpy chip mixing/dj upbeat break-beat experimental quirky
tracks.title: Laughing all the way
tracks.description: LATW is an up-beat chip-tune break-beat experiment holding many different parts/transitions.  The sharp chirpy chip-leads play through as bass-thunder-omg blasts along with some dj-style mixing; overloading the senses with an all around fun experience.

tracks.tag_list: slenderman zombies horror creepy dark dangerous
tracks.title: Kreepor
tracks.description: A dark, disturbing ambiance casts over you as this song protrudes into your psyche.  More of a mood-setter, this piece promises to build an atmosphere of lurking evil in the midst.

tracks.tag_list: loops funky breaks repetitive short
tracks.title: Kickit Homeboy!
tracks.description: Kickit Homeboy! is a fun filled break-beat style song, while short, can be used a variety of different ways to express a funky bit of excitement!

tracks.tag_list: amateur fantasy dragons heros rpg sythns strings horns
tracks.title: The Uncertain Hero
tracks.description: The song would do well in any Fantasy Game (especially RPG's) perhaps a good castle song, or even a good battle song.   When I wrote it, however, I thought of a hero coming to battle a large dragon.  The different parts were to emphasize the introduction of the Hero and the Dragon, and then climax to the final battle.  Will the hero lose, or survive?  Listen to find out!

tracks.tag_list: hard thumping rave intense action fast-paced hardcore
tracks.title: Hard Noise
tracks.description: Hard Noise has a rough, rugged, fast paced techno sound that will keep your blood pumping.  While I love to dance to this tune, I can see this in an intense action game that would only compliment the action; not over-take it.  The song has a "Here it comes" feel then a huge DROP into intense musical action.

tracks.tag_list: 8bit retro techno repetitive sloppy
tracks.title: Gameboy
tracks.description: "Gameboy" is a song that was inspired by the 8 bit sounds I have enjoyed from this vintage handheld gaming machine. Take a journey through 8-bit and beyond. Anything celebrating retro gaming would be well complimented by this "vintage" tune. The tune plays over and over again, and is rather happy, but each time it plays it comes in a bit more "modern" and more "modern" as it goes.

tracks.tag_list: dark suspensful anti-climactic serious mysterious slow jam
tracks.title: Forget
tracks.description: A slower song that gives the sense of mystery, while showing a building suspense which ultimately ends anti-climatically.

tracks.tag_list: happy joyful upbeat nodrums chiptune synths chirps
tracks.title: Finding Happiness (no-drums)
tracks.description: Finding Happiness without the drums.

tracks.tag_list: happy upbeat smile fortunate glad joyful synths arpeggio
tracks.title: Finding Happiness
tracks.description: A song about finding happiness. :-P

tracks.tag_list: Dark somber mysterious angsty damning doom slow progressive synths
tracks.title: Eternal
tracks.description: Eternal is a song I had written back in 2005. The song has a slower pace, but gives you the feeling of something that something mysterious is going on. The slow melody and progressive percussion changes make this one perfect for anything transitional. The beat consists of a slow break-beat pattern, mixed with thick strings and other synth sounds. This song is free to use for anyone as long as I am given credit and my site is mentioned.

tracks.tag_list: slow deep strange mystery somber angry ambient grave saddening dark
tracks.title: Enrolled
tracks.description: Enrolled is a slow song with a strong melody that bends and twists through an uneven, deep chasm of strong ambiance.  Drums kick in and out in this one.  Definitely different.

tracks.tag_list: war mysterious adventourous fun
tracks.title: Emergence
tracks.description: Emergence is a fast-paced, rich electronic ensemble inspired of music from the Castlevania(tm) series(80-90s'), but with a more mysterious twist.  The song is filled with every part necessary, and endlessly loops.  It has slow ambient bridges, a wonderful melodic verse and a hard hitting chorus that will get stuck in your head!

tracks.tag_list: fun quirky sci-fi
tracks.title: March of the Droids
tracks.description: The word is out, the droids are coming, and there's nothing you can do to stop them. One by one, single file, everyone will fall to the long arm of the robots! As the music strolls along, you'll know that you have no chance for survival. Systemically all will fall.  This song is an updated version of "curious tragedy" (repackaged and named properly)

tracks.tag_list: slow rts delayers synths vox
tracks.title: Warfield
tracks.description: The troops are being rallied, the bunker is being built, and the enemy is coming on the horizon.  Every minute counts, as you race to bring everyone together and fight!  This song reminds me very much of something I'd hear in an RTS game(during base building parts), however a slow paced, suspenseful song could be used for many things.

tracks.tag_list: fast-paced progressive intense action-packed etho minecraft chasing
tracks.title: Drifted
tracks.description: Popularized by minecraft enthusiasts, Drifted is a fast-paced progressive song that builds up to an intense finale.  The song would go well in any action packed game or video pushing an important point.  The song keeps you interested from start to finish!  Thank you, and enjoy!

tracks.tag_list: somber sad synths strong emotional hopeful loss techno
tracks.title: Down
tracks.description: A sad, sad song that takes you through strong emotions of loss, yet a chance for hope.

tracks.tag_list: modplug_tracker quirky techno repetitive crawling funky skippy
tracks.title: Descent
tracks.description: Funky synths mixed with a melodic exploration into the keys of descent. This song would be great for a video, commercial, or anything else that needs a bit of funk mixed with a melody that crawls the scales. The fast pace definately puts it into the "Exciting" category. The variations take you on a descent into a musical fantasy filled by a techno-driven engine.

tracks.tag_list: reverb rock industrial garage wailing tempochanges distortion distorted loud
tracks.title: Dead Waiting
tracks.description: Dead Waiting is a rock/metal tune that uses real drum kit sounds and guitar synths.  The song starts off slow and speeds up as time progresses.  It would be great to use for a dark game or video where the focus is surely something dreary.  The word "waiting" is used because it does give the sense that something ominous is near, and that something must be done. The intensity of the song changes back and fourth, allowing for a theme to show both climax and suspense.

tracks.tag_list: techno slow mysterious quirky weird
tracks.title: Cyber Advance
tracks.description: This one is a little slow but steady, increasing and building unto an triumphant melody.   A "tense" melody starts it off and carries it into the unknown.  As the song progresses a strong melody brings in presence, then ending the song with a sense of victory.

tracks.tag_list: ambient background clever sneaky transcending quirky slow jam
tracks.title: Conspiracy
tracks.description: The song includes a slow opener, and transcends into the strong theme of espionage.  It's clever, sneaky, and hides well into the background.  Rolling at the possible speed of your heart rate, it slowly builds into an anti-climactic chorus.  Where it ends, you just have to find out..

tracks.tag_list: weird strange quirky techno moody conflicting patterns experimental
tracks.title: Crushed out
tracks.description: This pace of the song gives the feeling of waiting, or striding through something slightly ominous.  The application of this song is where it just enhances the mood of the project, as it is quite non-intrusive in nature. It seamlessly loops, with giving the affect that it's much longer than it actually is.

tracks.tag_list: tracker rpg boss battle fighting burning techno repetetive background music
tracks.title: Burning
tracks.description: "Burning" was inspired by battle-music found in RPG games. If you are working on an RPG and am interested in having some intense fighting music look no further! This song has an epic feel to it, while it is simple and short. The intensity of the song varies, but it is more or less a good fighting song, not really a boss battle.

tracks.tag_list: fastpaced exciting intense techno
tracks.title: Bring em' out!
tracks.description: Whew! This one is intense!  A very fast paced tuned, similar to "Driven" - but with a more raw approach.  The song is short at two minute songs, and has several different parts and variations giving you the sensation that you're kicking ass and kicking it fast!

tracks.tag_list: techno fastpaced background music repetitive tracker modplug
tracks.title: Breakin' Thru
tracks.description: "Breakin Thru" is a fast-paced techno song good for a demo or a fast paced action game.  The melody is quite strong but very capable of being a supplement to adding intensity to your game or demo.  Feel free to use this however you'd like, so long as you give me credit by linking to my website!

tracks.tag_list: ambient slow somber
tracks.title: Fade
tracks.description: Fade is a slow song with an ambient intro. It includes a simple drum pattern that drives the melodies through and gives the sense as if you were waiting for something to happen.
